# Healthcare Platform Backend — Windsurf Rules

## Project
NestJS 11 REST API | MongoDB via Mongoose 9 | TypeScript 5 | Domain-Driven Design

## Architecture — enforce this strictly
```
HTTP → Controller → Service → Repository → MongoDB
```
- Controllers: HTTP only, no business logic
- Services: business logic, calls Repository
- Repositories: all Mongoose queries live here
- Schemas: `src/schemas/` (shared across domains)
- Helper services: utility/formatting logic within a domain, injected by Service

## File conventions
| Artifact | Path | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Schema | `src/schemas/<singular>.schema.ts` | `hospital.schema.ts` |
| Repository | `src/repositories/<singular>.repository.ts` | `hospital.repository.ts` |
| Module folder | `src/<plural>/` | `hospitals/` |
| Module file | `src/<plural>/<plural>.module.ts` | `hospitals.module.ts` |
| Controller | `src/<plural>/<plural>.controller.ts` | `hospitals.controller.ts` |
| Service | `src/<plural>/<plural>.service.ts` | `hospitals.service.ts` |
| Helper | `src/<plural>/<plural>-helper.service.ts` | `hospitals-helper.service.ts` |

## Mongoose 9 — critical rules
- `FilterQuery` was **removed** — use `object` for filter parameters
- `UpdateQuery` exists — import as `import type { UpdateQuery } from 'mongoose'`
- `moduleResolution: nodenext` is active

## Module wiring (every domain module must follow this)
```typescript
@Module({
  imports: [MongooseModule.forFeature([{ name: Entity.name, schema: EntitySchema }])],
  controllers: [EntityController],
  providers: [EntityService, EntityHelperService, EntityRepository],
  exports: [EntityRepository],
})
```

## Route ordering — specific before wildcard
```typescript
@Get('available')          // ✅ specific first
@Get('category/:cat')      // ✅ specific first
@Get(':id')                // ✅ wildcard last
```

## Never do
- Query the DB in a Service (use the Repository)
- Import a Service from another domain (export and use the Repository)
- Add `FilterQuery` from mongoose (removed in v9)
- Add DTOs or validation pipes unless explicitly asked

## Run locally
```bash
npm install && cp .env.example .env
# set MONGODB_URI in .env
npm run start:dev
```
